1
00:00:19,095 --> 00:00:23,700
[1056 AM Tokai]

2
00:00:23,700 --> 00:00:25,861
<i>This Dreams versus Vikings game</i>

3
00:00:25,861 --> 00:00:30,151
<i>is brought to you from the Dreams' very own
Toyohashi Yaoshima Dome.</i>

4
00:00:30,879 --> 00:00:35,419
The score is 8 to 2.
The Dreams are trailing by 6 runs.

5
00:01:08,653 --> 00:01:10,617
- Good work.
- Good work.

6
00:01:10,617 --> 00:01:12,750
Good work.

7
00:01:14,390 --> 00:01:17,440
[President of Baseball Operations (POBO)]

8
00:01:23,636 --> 00:01:26,079
<i>It's the final game between the Dreams,
who are in last place this season,</i>

9
00:01:26,079 --> 00:01:30,806
<i>and the Vikings, who have already secured
a spot in the Climax Series.</i>

10
00:01:32,169 --> 00:01:33,777
Batting third is Tanigaki.

11
00:01:33,777 --> 00:01:36,924
He previously hit a line drive
to second base.

12
00:01:38,438 --> 00:01:40,710
Well, that was a jammed hit.

13
00:01:40,710 --> 00:01:44,499
The shortstop handles it lightly,
and throws to first.

14
00:01:44,499 --> 00:01:46,562
Bottom of the 6th, two outs,
no runners on base.

15
00:01:46,562 --> 00:01:49,470
The Dreams are down six runs.

16
00:01:49,470 --> 00:01:55,186
Kudo! Kudo! Kudo! Kudo! Kudo!

17
00:01:55,186 --> 00:01:57,765
<i>Batting cleanup, left fielder Kudo.</i>

18
00:01:57,765 --> 00:01:58,745
[Tatsuya Kudo]

19
00:01:59,600 --> 00:02:02,631
Stepping up to plate
with the crowd cheering for him

20
00:02:02,631 --> 00:02:05,427
is Dreams' slugger, Kudo.

21
00:02:09,995 --> 00:02:12,952
Hit it out of the park, Kudo!

22
00:02:12,952 --> 00:02:15,292
His appearance alone has the crowd roaring.

23
00:02:15,292 --> 00:02:19,831
Fans have high hopes for Kudo's swing.

24
00:02:19,831 --> 00:02:22,995
Kudo is 1-for-2 today.

25
00:02:22,995 --> 00:02:25,639
If he gets a hit here,
the dugout will liven up.

26
00:02:25,639 --> 00:02:29,983
Hit it out of the park, Kudo! Kudo! Kudo!

27
00:02:37,412 --> 00:02:40,074
He hit it! Did it go?

28
00:02:40,074 --> 00:02:42,338
The ball is flying far!

29
00:02:42,338 --> 00:02:44,302
It's in! It's in!

30
00:02:44,302 --> 00:02:48,471
The ball goes straight
to the left field stands!

31
00:02:48,471 --> 00:02:52,608
A defiant home run from cleanup hitter Kudo.

32
00:02:52,608 --> 00:02:55,323
This is his 30th home run of the season,

33
00:02:55,323 --> 00:02:57,791
putting him third in the home run race!

34
00:02:57,791 --> 00:03:00,410
What a dazzling hit that was.

35
00:03:00,410 --> 00:03:01,772
Indeed.

36
00:03:01,772 --> 00:03:06,475
He knew it was out of there
the moment he hit it.

37
00:03:06,475 --> 00:03:08,983
He truly is a reliable presence

38
00:03:08,983 --> 00:03:11,781
throughout this team's rough season.

39
00:03:13,573 --> 00:03:15,815
In the bottom of the 6th,
Kudo's solo home run

40
00:03:15,815 --> 00:03:18,946
brings the Dreams to five runs.

41
00:03:36,180 --> 00:03:39,040
[The Kudo Burger: Filling, and satisfying!]

42
00:04:05,481 --> 00:04:09,626
Leading off the 7th for the Vikings,
is their 5th batter, Nomura.

43
00:04:12,744 --> 00:04:15,100
On the mound is the starting pitcher, Kijima.

44
00:04:15,100 --> 00:04:17,448
He has already thrown over 90 pitches.

45
00:04:17,448 --> 00:04:20,420
Hit it out of the park, Nomura!

46
00:04:21,686 --> 00:04:25,191
Oh no, the ball got away!

47
00:04:25,191 --> 00:04:27,203
- It's a dead ball!
- Hey!

48
00:04:27,203 --> 00:04:28,950
Don't hit him over the score!

49
00:04:28,950 --> 00:04:30,410
Yeah, watch it!

50
00:04:30,410 --> 00:04:35,263
Looks like the Vikings' dugout
is getting a bit heated.

51
00:04:41,604 --> 00:04:43,700
Catch it!

52
00:04:43,700 --> 00:04:47,614
Coach! Please change the pitcher already!

53
00:04:51,222 --> 00:04:54,768
<i>Batting 6th, designated hitter, Allen.</i>

54
00:04:58,771 --> 00:05:00,106
Hey!

55
00:05:00,106 --> 00:05:04,775
Why is a useless hitting coach
interfering with a pitching change?

56
00:05:04,775 --> 00:05:06,016
Huh?

57
00:05:06,016 --> 00:05:10,171
Coach, I'll decide when we change pitchers.

58
00:05:10,171 --> 00:05:13,348
Well, I say we change. How about it, Coach?

59
00:05:13,348 --> 00:05:14,917
Stay out of my lane!

60
00:05:14,917 --> 00:05:16,660
What? Then change him already! Hear me?

61
00:05:16,660 --> 00:05:17,988
What?

62
00:05:17,988 --> 00:05:19,049
Coach, please...

63
00:05:19,049 --> 00:05:20,789
Can it!

64
00:05:21,843 --> 00:05:23,755
Now sit your asses back down.

65
00:05:28,859 --> 00:05:31,387
The Dreams can't give up any more runs.

66
00:05:31,387 --> 00:05:36,017
Kijima on the mound.
Can he get out of this jam?

67
00:05:41,640 --> 00:05:44,500
He's hit it! The ball goes to center field!

68
00:05:44,500 --> 00:05:48,267
He comes forward, and the ball has dropped!

69
00:05:48,267 --> 00:05:50,894
That's a clean hit.

70
00:05:51,961 --> 00:05:55,187
Did he misjudge the trajectory of that hit?

71
00:05:55,187 --> 00:05:58,082
I swear that was an out in the making.

72
00:05:58,082 --> 00:06:01,012
Their pitcher must be frustrated.

73
00:06:07,708 --> 00:06:09,203
The count's at three balls.

74
00:06:09,203 --> 00:06:12,096
Kijima's pitching marathon continues.

75
00:06:12,096 --> 00:06:14,503
Kijima's a veteran getting on in the years.

76
00:06:14,503 --> 00:06:17,597
The dugout ought to consider
swapping pitchers.

77
00:06:17,597 --> 00:06:19,495
This one goes right to second base.

78
00:06:19,495 --> 00:06:21,181
And it's a glove fumble!

79
00:06:21,181 --> 00:06:25,255
His throw is way off.
The ball goes to left field!

80
00:06:25,255 --> 00:06:28,377
Wow, I can't believe what I just witnessed.

81
00:06:28,377 --> 00:06:30,948
This is practically a sandlot game.

82
00:06:30,948 --> 00:06:34,977
Nomura scores in the meantime!
The Vikings score another run!

83
00:06:36,577 --> 00:06:40,009
What are you doing? Get it together!

84
00:06:40,780 --> 00:06:42,785
The score is now 9 to 3.

85
00:06:42,785 --> 00:06:47,014
The Vikings are once again up six runs.

86
00:06:50,481 --> 00:06:53,705
Seriously? Damn it...

87
00:06:54,758 --> 00:06:57,083
It's the final game of the season,

88
00:06:57,083 --> 00:07:01,047
and fans are already leaving the stadium.

89
00:07:05,392 --> 00:07:07,905
- Pitcher change.
- Yes, sir.

90
00:07:07,905 --> 00:07:10,743
<i>Your attention, please.</i>

91
00:07:10,743 --> 00:07:15,025
<i>Now pitching for the Dreams, #22 Suzuki.</i>

92
00:07:15,025 --> 00:07:17,094
<i>#22 Suzuki.</i>

93
00:07:17,094 --> 00:07:18,624
<i>#22 Suzuki.</i>

94
00:07:18,624 --> 00:07:20,970
I can't blame paying fans for leaving

95
00:07:20,970 --> 00:07:23,987
when their home team is absolutely fumbling.

96
00:07:31,880 --> 00:07:34,900
<i>Dreamers, give it up for our Lucky Sevens!</i>

97
00:07:56,487 --> 00:08:00,165
That guy who got in through connections
is slacking!

98
00:08:02,720 --> 00:08:04,640
I'm so tired.

99
00:08:05,486 --> 00:08:08,418
A mascot shouldn't be giving up!

100
00:08:08,418 --> 00:08:10,151
Woah, hey! Watch it!

101
00:08:10,151 --> 00:08:12,219
Why do I have to wear this thing?

102
00:08:12,219 --> 00:08:14,513
Because our usual guy is out sick.

103
00:08:14,513 --> 00:08:16,916
Well, I'm going to be out sick from the heat.

104
00:08:16,916 --> 00:08:18,876
At least we're not outdoors.

105
00:08:18,876 --> 00:08:20,357
Yeah? You try wearing this.

106
00:08:20,357 --> 00:08:23,022
Come on, no more complaining.

107
00:08:23,022 --> 00:08:25,092
- Move it.
- Hey, careful!

108
00:08:25,092 --> 00:08:26,243
- I'm hydrating!
- Hurry up!

109
00:08:26,243 --> 00:08:27,883
Ms. President! Ms. President!

110
00:08:27,883 --> 00:08:30,641
We've got a problem, ma'am!

111
00:08:31,513 --> 00:08:32,865
<i>What's wrong, Dreams?</i>

112
00:08:32,865 --> 00:08:34,939
<i>Was there a conflict within the team?</i>

113
00:08:34,939 --> 00:08:38,336
<i>How disgraceful. This team is finished.</i>

114
00:08:38,336 --> 00:08:41,315
What do they think they're doing?

115
00:08:41,315 --> 00:08:42,806
- Let's go!
- Huh?

116
00:08:42,806 --> 00:08:43,786
Hurry!

117
00:08:43,786 --> 00:08:45,447
Hey, hey, hey, hey, hey!

118
00:08:45,447 --> 00:08:47,085
Hey! Hey, hey, wait!

119
00:08:47,085 --> 00:08:48,644
- My water! Water!
- Let's go!

120
00:08:48,644 --> 00:08:50,899
Someone! Hey!

121
00:08:59,873 --> 00:09:01,589
Stop it!

122
00:09:02,717 --> 00:09:04,975
Stop fighting!

123
00:09:19,936 --> 00:09:22,266
Please calm down!

124
00:09:23,324 --> 00:09:24,929
Calm down!

125
00:09:24,929 --> 00:09:26,991
Everyone!

126
00:09:26,991 --> 00:09:30,101
Hey! Please calm down!

127
00:09:30,101 --> 00:09:32,106
Calm down!

128
00:09:39,296 --> 00:09:42,173
There are children watching!

129
00:09:42,173 --> 00:09:44,537
Don't disappoint them!

130
00:09:46,533 --> 00:09:48,948
It's the last game of the year.

131
00:09:56,347 --> 00:09:58,416
What are you doing, seriously?

132
00:09:58,416 --> 00:09:59,936
Geez.

133
00:09:59,936 --> 00:10:03,146
- You started it.
- Oh, yeah?

134
00:10:03,146 --> 00:10:04,305
Move it.

135
00:10:05,162 --> 00:10:07,129
<i>The game has ended.</i>

136
00:10:07,129 --> 00:10:10,675
- Thank you.
- <i>Today's score is 14 to 3.</i>

137
00:10:10,675 --> 00:10:13,279
<i>The Vikings have won.</i>

138
00:10:13,279 --> 00:10:16,229
<i>Winning pitcher, Onizuka.</i>

139
00:10:16,229 --> 00:10:19,428
<i>Winning pitcher, Onizuka.</i>

140
00:10:19,428 --> 00:10:22,234
<i>Losing pitcher, Kijima.</i>

141
00:10:22,234 --> 00:10:25,056
<i>Losing pitcher, Kijima.</i>

142
00:10:29,260 --> 00:10:31,573
Why can't we win?

143
00:11:06,274 --> 00:11:08,814
It's not our fault.

144
00:11:08,814 --> 00:11:11,202
The players are the ones playing the games.

145
00:11:11,202 --> 00:11:12,275
Exactly.

146
00:11:12,275 --> 00:11:14,862
It's not fair to blame us.

147
00:11:14,862 --> 00:11:16,594
Alright everyone, let's drink the night away.

148
00:11:16,594 --> 00:11:18,071
Yeah.

149
00:11:18,071 --> 00:11:20,381
- Kurokawa, you drink too!
- I am, I am.

150
00:11:20,381 --> 00:11:22,701
Maybe our cheapskate owner is to blame?

151
00:11:22,701 --> 00:11:23,712
You may be right.

152
00:11:23,712 --> 00:11:26,624
Next year, let's aim for 5th place!

153
00:11:26,624 --> 00:11:28,122
- 5th place!
- Perfect!

154
00:11:28,122 --> 00:11:30,808
- Excellent.
- Great idea.

155
00:11:30,808 --> 00:11:34,630
Why're you all laughing, huh?

156
00:11:34,630 --> 00:11:36,364
Ma'am, you're drinking too much.

157
00:11:36,364 --> 00:11:38,572
We lost, and you all are laughing.

158
00:11:38,572 --> 00:11:41,363
This is why we're always in last place!

159
00:11:41,363 --> 00:11:44,145
Oh no, the alcohol monster
is about to go on a rampage!

160
00:11:44,145 --> 00:11:45,894
Someone, take her drink away!

161
00:11:45,894 --> 00:11:47,639
Huh? Me?

162
00:11:47,639 --> 00:11:50,001
Okay, Prez. Let's put that down for a second.

163
00:11:50,001 --> 00:11:51,538
Don't touch me, Nepo hire!

164
00:11:51,538 --> 00:11:52,922
Ow!

165
00:11:53,811 --> 00:11:56,935
Now, now, folks. Let's calm down.

166
00:11:56,935 --> 00:11:57,981
Everyone...

167
00:11:57,981 --> 00:12:00,193
What's wrong, GM?

168
00:12:00,193 --> 00:12:06,104
Well, the Dreams this year
only managed 56 wins.

169
00:12:06,104 --> 00:12:08,344
Last year we secured 59 wins.

170
00:12:08,344 --> 00:12:11,291
- So, we had 3 fewer wins.
- That's what it is.

171
00:12:11,291 --> 00:12:12,816
That's true.

172
00:12:12,816 --> 00:12:14,351
I...

173
00:12:15,028 --> 00:12:16,724
have decided to resign as GM!

174
00:12:16,724 --> 00:12:17,873
Huh?

175
00:12:17,873 --> 00:12:19,602
What are you talking about?

176
00:12:19,602 --> 00:12:21,841
I apologize for the delay
in making this decision.

177
00:12:21,841 --> 00:12:23,939
Well then, I'll be taking my leave!

178
00:12:23,939 --> 00:12:26,136
Whoa, whoa, whoa! Wait!

179
00:12:26,136 --> 00:12:28,381
GM, please wait!

180
00:12:29,066 --> 00:12:31,212
- What? What's wrong?
- Scary, scary, scary.

181
00:12:32,610 --> 00:12:33,981
He's fast.

182
00:12:33,981 --> 00:12:35,906
Just wait a minute!

183
00:12:36,700 --> 00:12:37,753
Just a moment.

184
00:12:37,753 --> 00:12:39,027
- More alcohol!
- Ouch.

185
00:12:39,027 --> 00:12:39,992
Alcohol!

186
00:12:39,992 --> 00:12:42,315
Let's drink! Drink, drink, drink!

187
00:12:42,315 --> 00:12:44,199
Slow down, Prez.

188
00:12:44,199 --> 00:12:45,187
No drinking it straight.

189
00:12:45,187 --> 00:12:46,984
She's got a strong grip.

190
00:12:46,984 --> 00:12:49,506
Drink, drink, drink!

191
00:12:49,506 --> 00:12:51,388
This isn't alcohol!

192
00:12:51,388 --> 00:12:52,978
- Were you even listening?
- Ow, ow!

193
00:12:52,978 --> 00:12:54,960
- I said, alcohol.
- I thought water would help.

194
00:12:54,960 --> 00:12:56,770
- Alcohol!
- Ow, ow...

195
00:12:56,770 --> 00:12:59,036
My ear's gonna fall off!
It's gonna rip off!

196
00:12:59,036 --> 00:13:00,449
- Anyone got more alcohol?
- Is my ear still there?

197
00:13:00,449 --> 00:13:02,871
- Let's calm down.
- Where's the alcohol?

198
00:13:30,770 --> 00:13:33,756
Maybe I should quit too...

199
00:13:45,890 --> 00:13:47,645
I know.

200
00:13:48,808 --> 00:13:50,613
I'm not quitting.

201
00:13:53,224 --> 00:13:57,064
How do you plan to utilize
your previous work experience?

202
00:13:57,064 --> 00:13:59,561
I will leverage my experience
as a management consultant

203
00:13:59,561 --> 00:14:02,685
to assign the right people
to the right positions.

204
00:14:03,504 --> 00:14:06,810
As I've been a player, coach, and manager,

205
00:14:06,810 --> 00:14:08,867
I believe in incorporating many opinions

206
00:14:08,867 --> 00:14:11,770
from those directly on the field.

207
00:14:13,155 --> 00:14:16,353
Which of them will be the new GM?

208
00:14:17,148 --> 00:14:19,041
They're both excellent,
so it's a tough choice.

209
00:14:19,041 --> 00:14:20,706
Indeed.

210
00:14:20,706 --> 00:14:23,341
- There's still an applicant left.
- What?

211
00:14:23,341 --> 00:14:24,649
Oh, right.

212
00:14:25,339 --> 00:14:26,968
Come on in.

213
00:14:29,910 --> 00:14:31,616
Excuse me.

214
00:14:41,966 --> 00:14:43,812
Please have a seat.

215
00:14:44,512 --> 00:14:45,861
Thank you.

216
00:14:48,487 --> 00:14:50,739
Mr. Jun Sakurazaki.

217
00:14:50,739 --> 00:14:56,329
You were a GM for ice hockey, volleyball,
and rugby, correct?

218
00:14:57,182 --> 00:14:58,722
Yes.

219
00:14:58,722 --> 00:15:01,907
And you're currently unemployed?

220
00:15:01,907 --> 00:15:03,261
Yes.

221
00:15:04,815 --> 00:15:07,926
Have you ever watched a Dreams game?

222
00:15:07,926 --> 00:15:11,156
I've watched my fair share of edited clips.

223
00:15:11,156 --> 00:15:13,202
Ah, those.

224
00:15:13,202 --> 00:15:15,867
If only they weren't so malicious.

225
00:15:15,867 --> 00:15:19,288
Only our losing games get uploaded.

226
00:15:19,288 --> 00:15:23,142
Those sorts of videos
will only continue to increase.

227
00:15:23,142 --> 00:15:25,258
Huh? What do you mean?

228
00:15:26,195 --> 00:15:28,268
For the next decade,

229
00:15:29,131 --> 00:15:30,949
your team may remain in last place.

230
00:15:30,949 --> 00:15:32,117
What?

231
00:15:32,117 --> 00:15:33,680
What are you talking about?

232
00:15:33,680 --> 00:15:34,692
Presumptuous.

233
00:15:34,692 --> 00:15:36,538
Can you back your claim in any way?

234
00:15:36,538 --> 00:15:38,881
What do you know of the Dreams?

235
00:15:38,881 --> 00:15:39,909
Now, now, now...

236
00:15:40,924 --> 00:15:42,544
I know enough.

237
00:15:42,544 --> 00:15:44,804
Oh, really? Then go on, tell us.

238
00:15:44,804 --> 00:15:46,322
- Hey.
- Calm down.

239
00:15:46,322 --> 00:15:48,965
The coaches fight amongst themselves.

240
00:15:48,965 --> 00:15:50,355
Huh?

241
00:15:52,555 --> 00:15:55,648
The manager is looked down upon.

242
00:15:57,125 --> 00:16:01,471
The players are ashamed of their own team.

243
00:16:03,506 --> 00:16:08,336
Team management is outdated,
and relies solely on instinct.

244
00:16:09,700 --> 00:16:11,150
And...

245
00:16:11,150 --> 00:16:12,998
- We've heard enough.
- Hey, now.

246
00:16:12,998 --> 00:16:15,074
- Thank you for your time today.
- Prez.

247
00:16:15,074 --> 00:16:16,637
We'll keep your resume on record.

248
00:16:16,637 --> 00:16:18,102
Keep an ear out for your results.

249
00:16:18,102 --> 00:16:20,048
- Wait!
- Please leave.

250
00:16:20,048 --> 00:16:22,098
The exit is right that way.

251
00:16:22,984 --> 00:16:24,685
Then if you'll excuse me.

252
00:16:32,677 --> 00:16:35,171
You missed a chance to win.

253
00:16:38,832 --> 00:16:40,472
What?

254
00:16:43,566 --> 00:16:45,841
What's with that guy?

255
00:16:59,678 --> 00:17:02,501
He doesn't know a thing about baseball.

256
00:17:02,501 --> 00:17:04,132
He's so annoying!

257
00:17:04,132 --> 00:17:06,152
And what's with the nonchalant face?

258
00:17:13,436 --> 00:17:15,309
Mr. Sakurazaki.

259
00:17:17,488 --> 00:17:20,362
Do the Dreams have any strengths to them?

260
00:17:20,362 --> 00:17:22,885
What is it you want for this team?

261
00:17:23,934 --> 00:17:26,679
I want them to win, of course.

262
00:17:26,679 --> 00:17:28,803
Does everyone see eye-to-eye with you?

263
00:17:28,803 --> 00:17:30,161
Huh?

264
00:17:31,083 --> 00:17:32,795
What do you mean?

265
00:17:37,214 --> 00:17:39,407
I mean nothing more than just that.

266
00:17:49,473 --> 00:17:51,998
What the heck was he talking about?

267
00:17:51,998 --> 00:17:55,401
We're united! We're one team!

268
00:17:59,051 --> 00:18:00,636
Hey, hey!

269
00:18:00,636 --> 00:18:01,837
Our dumplings are burning.

270
00:18:01,837 --> 00:18:04,107
Blame that on the dumplings.

271
00:18:04,107 --> 00:18:06,972
You're always full of sophistry.

272
00:18:06,972 --> 00:18:08,756
Hey, turn off the heat.

273
00:18:09,562 --> 00:18:12,134
He talks big for a baseball amateur.

274
00:18:12,134 --> 00:18:13,467
Sorry, who?

275
00:18:13,467 --> 00:18:16,446
Haven't you been listening?
The guy I interviewed!

276
00:18:16,446 --> 00:18:19,009
You're lashing out at everyone,
so I don't know!

277
00:18:19,009 --> 00:18:20,453
Listen up.

278
00:18:20,453 --> 00:18:24,144
I love the Dreams more than anyone.

279
00:18:24,144 --> 00:18:25,882
I don't care! Rejected!

280
00:18:25,882 --> 00:18:28,544
Why do I have to be interviewed
by my sister?

281
00:18:28,544 --> 00:18:31,754
Well, he's probably wondering
why he was interviewed

282
00:18:31,754 --> 00:18:35,107
by a lady who's never even played baseball.

283
00:18:35,107 --> 00:18:36,545
Damn it.

284
00:18:37,342 --> 00:18:39,149
I win.

285
00:18:39,149 --> 00:18:41,674
No, I win. Did you see that chug just now?

286
00:18:41,674 --> 00:18:43,093
No, but it's my win.

287
00:18:43,093 --> 00:18:45,418
- I win!
- Careful, I'm cooking.

288
00:18:45,418 --> 00:18:46,710
This girl...

289
00:18:46,710 --> 00:18:48,536
So, you're not hiring him?

290
00:18:48,536 --> 00:18:49,645
Of course not!

291
00:18:49,645 --> 00:18:53,977
If I worked with a guy like that,
I'd catch his apathetic face.

292
00:18:53,977 --> 00:18:55,429
Hey.

293
00:18:55,429 --> 00:18:58,748
Don't burn it this time.

294
00:18:58,748 --> 00:19:00,666
Yeah, yeah.

295
00:19:00,666 --> 00:19:02,409
Easy!

296
00:19:23,279 --> 00:19:26,187
Alright, has everyone gathered?

297
00:19:26,187 --> 00:19:28,101
Good morning.

298
00:19:28,101 --> 00:19:30,558
- Morning!
- Sorry I'm late. There was an accident...

299
00:19:30,558 --> 00:19:33,375
I'd like to introduce
a very important person.

300
00:19:33,375 --> 00:19:35,127
Charmed already?

301
00:19:35,127 --> 00:19:36,818
Oh, how embarrassing!

302
00:19:36,818 --> 00:19:39,975
While he may not be an expert in baseball,

303
00:19:39,975 --> 00:19:46,217
he has led many other athletes to victory.

304
00:19:46,217 --> 00:19:50,282
Please welcome our new GM, Jun Sakurazaki.

305
00:19:51,738 --> 00:19:54,031
Hello, everyone.

306
00:19:54,031 --> 00:19:56,929
I am Jun Sakurazaki, the new GM.

307
00:19:57,806 --> 00:20:01,011
I look forward to working with you all.

308
00:20:02,670 --> 00:20:05,039
Welcome, GM!

309
00:20:05,039 --> 00:20:08,863
Our new GM! He's so cool!

310
00:20:12,002 --> 00:20:14,797
Why did you choose him?

311
00:20:14,797 --> 00:20:18,147
He has many victories under his belt.

312
00:20:18,147 --> 00:20:20,923
He's an exceptional man, I'd say.

313
00:20:20,923 --> 00:20:22,241
But that person...

314
00:20:22,241 --> 00:20:25,683
Are you dissatisfied with my decision?

315
00:20:25,683 --> 00:20:28,773
No, it's not that. It's just, he...

316
00:20:28,773 --> 00:20:29,871
He has no team spirit.

317
00:20:29,871 --> 00:20:35,083
He's a necessary asset for the Dreams.

318
00:20:35,083 --> 00:20:36,744
Right?

319
00:20:37,589 --> 00:20:39,598
Right?

320
00:20:40,627 --> 00:20:42,051
Yes, sir.

321
00:21:04,326 --> 00:21:05,992
Ouch!

322
00:21:27,194 --> 00:21:30,226
Practicing already?
It's like you want to make a fortune.

323
00:21:30,226 --> 00:21:33,303
Hey, the feeling's mutual, isn't it?

324
00:21:33,303 --> 00:21:37,955
You're the only pitcher who throws
right after the season, Kijima.

325
00:21:38,605 --> 00:21:42,269
I'm challenging myself
to a new breaking ball.

326
00:21:42,269 --> 00:21:43,979
At this age, no less.

327
00:21:44,656 --> 00:21:47,233
You're so ambitious.

328
00:21:48,479 --> 00:21:50,997
Then I'll hit even better,

329
00:21:50,997 --> 00:21:54,119
and make you the winning pitcher, Kijima.

330
00:21:54,119 --> 00:21:56,501
Really now.

331
00:21:56,501 --> 00:21:58,735
I'll keep my expectations low.

332
00:22:06,775 --> 00:22:08,212
Come on in.

333
00:22:09,549 --> 00:22:12,605
Good afternoon, sir.

334
00:22:13,962 --> 00:22:15,636
What do you want?

335
00:22:17,311 --> 00:22:20,761
As an old-timer,
I know everything about our players.

336
00:22:20,761 --> 00:22:24,364
I believe I can help reassess our strengths.

337
00:22:26,727 --> 00:22:28,712
Is that so?

338
00:22:28,712 --> 00:22:30,626
Please give me a moment.

339
00:22:34,430 --> 00:22:38,282
Shohei's batting speed has increased.

340
00:22:38,282 --> 00:22:40,116
We can expect great things next year.

341
00:22:40,116 --> 00:22:44,027
Also, Rui is essential.

342
00:22:44,027 --> 00:22:46,667
He can't hit much, but he's fast.

343
00:22:46,667 --> 00:22:48,680
His defense is improving, too.

344
00:22:48,680 --> 00:22:51,222
I think he'll become a great player.

345
00:22:51,222 --> 00:22:52,257
Let's see, who else...

346
00:22:52,257 --> 00:22:55,340
How about the pitcher, Kijima?

347
00:22:56,067 --> 00:22:58,683
Kijima, huh...

348
00:22:58,683 --> 00:23:00,240
What is it?

349
00:23:01,489 --> 00:23:05,844
Honestly, I don't expect much from him.

350
00:23:05,844 --> 00:23:07,682
His performance is declining,

351
00:23:07,682 --> 00:23:10,399
and our younger guys find him hard to handle.

352
00:23:10,399 --> 00:23:12,918
He's too harsh on them.

353
00:23:13,566 --> 00:23:15,137
I see.

354
00:23:15,804 --> 00:23:18,110
Thank you.

355
00:23:18,110 --> 00:23:20,292
I have a plan of action now.

356
00:23:20,292 --> 00:23:21,357
That's good.

357
00:23:21,357 --> 00:23:24,887
[Pitchers]

358
00:23:40,263 --> 00:23:42,923
- What's with the "thumbs up"?
- Ow, ow, ow!

359
00:23:42,923 --> 00:23:45,778
Can't you learn to be serious for once?

360
00:23:45,778 --> 00:23:48,198
No matter what I do,
you just get mad at me.

361
00:23:48,198 --> 00:23:50,321
The Prez has been irritable lately.

362
00:23:50,321 --> 00:23:51,817
Oh? How so?

363
00:23:51,817 --> 00:23:54,000
You just proved your own point.

364
00:23:54,000 --> 00:23:56,310
Hear ye, hear ye, Ms. President.

365
00:23:56,310 --> 00:23:57,508
Here he comes!

366
00:23:57,508 --> 00:23:59,476
Coming through.

367
00:23:59,476 --> 00:24:02,033
- Now watch me, Ms. President.
- He's here.

368
00:24:02,033 --> 00:24:03,133
Smile!

369
00:24:03,133 --> 00:24:05,416
See? Let's go with a smile!

370
00:24:05,416 --> 00:24:06,802
Lift those corners and smile!

371
00:24:06,802 --> 00:24:09,554
- Yes, perfect!
- Enough with your fake smile, Kikuchi.

372
00:24:09,554 --> 00:24:11,101
We need none of it.

373
00:24:11,101 --> 00:24:12,538
- Are you okay? Are you okay?
- Ow, ow, ow.

374
00:24:12,538 --> 00:24:13,714
- Mr. Kikuchi!
- I took that with my face.

375
00:24:13,714 --> 00:24:15,607
- Where did Mr. Kikuchi go?
- I'm here.

376
00:24:15,607 --> 00:24:17,667
Huh? I am, aren't I?

377
00:24:17,667 --> 00:24:19,146
- I'm no ghost, right?
- Are you okay?

378
00:24:19,146 --> 00:24:21,764
- You can feel me, right?
- You're being dramatic!

379
00:24:21,764 --> 00:24:24,482
- Ow.
- Good morning.

380
00:24:24,482 --> 00:24:25,544
Good morning.

381
00:24:25,544 --> 00:24:27,530
- Good morning.
- Morning.

382
00:24:31,585 --> 00:24:34,002
I will inform you all of some decisions.

383
00:24:34,763 --> 00:24:37,744
If anyone has any objections,
please don't hesitate to speak up.

384
00:24:40,348 --> 00:24:42,560
First.

385
00:24:42,560 --> 00:24:44,158
The manager will remain.

386
00:24:44,158 --> 00:24:46,007
- What?
- No, but...

387
00:24:46,813 --> 00:24:48,960
President Negishi has given his approval.

388
00:24:48,960 --> 00:24:51,409
Mr. Nishida's contract
will be renewed three more years.

389
00:24:51,409 --> 00:24:53,296
- Three years?
- That's long.

390
00:24:53,296 --> 00:24:57,224
It's difficult to win and develop players
with a one-year contract.

391
00:24:57,224 --> 00:24:59,778
Did Mr. Negishi really agree to this?

392
00:24:59,778 --> 00:25:01,018
Yes.

393
00:25:01,018 --> 00:25:05,011
If Mr. Nishida respects the authority he has,

394
00:25:05,011 --> 00:25:06,991
he will become a good manager.

395
00:25:07,691 --> 00:25:09,719
Any objections?

396
00:25:09,719 --> 00:25:12,359
- Well...
- It seems there are none.

397
00:25:12,359 --> 00:25:14,479
Then my second plan of action.

398
00:25:14,479 --> 00:25:18,035
Though our coaches dispute with one another,

399
00:25:19,247 --> 00:25:21,321
all of them will remain.

400
00:25:23,099 --> 00:25:24,293
I object!

401
00:25:24,293 --> 00:25:25,437
That's ridiculous!

402
00:25:25,437 --> 00:25:28,187
You're the one who criticized our infighting.

403
00:25:29,849 --> 00:25:31,781
I don't mind them clashing.

404
00:25:31,781 --> 00:25:35,919
However, I'll have them compete
over their own stats.

405
00:25:35,919 --> 00:25:37,384
Now, now...

406
00:25:37,384 --> 00:25:39,825
Lastly, my third course of action.

407
00:25:39,825 --> 00:25:43,577
Something even President Negishi
initially opposed of.

408
00:25:47,924 --> 00:25:49,758
Kudo will be...

409
00:25:50,669 --> 00:25:52,329
traded away.

410
00:25:52,329 --> 00:25:53,143
Huh?

411
00:25:53,143 --> 00:25:56,720
Now hold on. He's our star player!

412
00:25:56,720 --> 00:25:59,504
I object to everything.
What are you thinking?

413
00:25:59,504 --> 00:26:03,072
Kudo is our cleanup hitter.

414
00:26:03,072 --> 00:26:06,684
Kudo will be traded.

415
00:26:08,238 --> 00:26:10,329
He's an indispensable asset.

416
00:26:10,329 --> 00:26:12,743
- I don't understand.
- GM.

417
00:26:12,743 --> 00:26:15,250
Did Mr. Negishi really agree to that?

418
00:26:15,250 --> 00:26:17,470
He would never.

419
00:26:17,470 --> 00:26:18,929
- He did.
- No!

420
00:26:18,929 --> 00:26:21,147
I have nothing but objections.

421
00:26:21,147 --> 00:26:22,841
In that case...

422
00:26:23,576 --> 00:26:25,353
Do you have an alternative plan?

423
00:26:25,353 --> 00:26:28,018
No, but I still object!

424
00:26:28,018 --> 00:26:29,119
Your objection is denied.

425
00:26:29,119 --> 00:26:30,481
Say what?

426
00:26:30,481 --> 00:26:32,069
Woah, woah, woah!

427
00:26:32,069 --> 00:26:33,929
This isn't a fistfight.

428
00:26:33,929 --> 00:26:36,743
Let's use our words.

429
00:26:38,499 --> 00:26:40,860
Ow!

430
00:26:40,860 --> 00:26:43,159
[The GM's talking about trading you away.]

431
00:26:43,159 --> 00:26:48,800
Kudo, what are your predictions
for strategies seen in the Climax Series?

432
00:26:48,800 --> 00:26:50,605
Great question.

433
00:26:50,605 --> 00:26:52,531
It's a short series,

434
00:26:52,531 --> 00:26:54,721
so teams will use their best pitchers a lot.

435
00:26:54,721 --> 00:26:58,427
I think batters will have
an especially tough time.

436
00:26:58,427 --> 00:26:59,968
I see.

437
00:26:59,968 --> 00:27:06,080
We'll continue with Kudo's predictions
after the commercial break.

438
00:27:06,080 --> 00:27:08,650
- We're in commercials.
- Copy that.

439
00:27:16,850 --> 00:27:19,530
[The GM's talking about trading you away.]

440
00:27:22,099 --> 00:27:24,603
Don't mess with me!

441
00:27:30,251 --> 00:27:33,580
Five seconds. Four, three.

442
00:27:35,331 --> 00:27:37,482
The professional baseball Climax Series
is about to begin.

443
00:27:37,482 --> 00:27:40,549
We're getting predictions
from the Dreams' Kudo and...

444
00:27:40,549 --> 00:27:44,965
I was able to keep batting
because I was with the Dreams.

445
00:27:46,765 --> 00:27:49,642
I can't imagine playing for another team.

446
00:27:49,642 --> 00:27:52,534
Tatsuya Kudo is a slugger for Samurai Japan.

447
00:27:52,534 --> 00:27:55,032
Yes. I know.

448
00:27:55,032 --> 00:27:57,190
It's not about knowing.

449
00:27:57,190 --> 00:27:59,196
I'm trading him.

450
00:28:00,489 --> 00:28:06,084
My dream is to have my number
retired by the Dreams.

451
00:28:07,626 --> 00:28:11,802
Why are you persisting, President Makita?

452
00:28:11,802 --> 00:28:13,753
I can act without your permission, no?

453
00:28:13,753 --> 00:28:15,417
Yes, however...

454
00:28:15,417 --> 00:28:20,910
Are you speaking out
because you think I'm a baseball amateur?

455
00:28:20,910 --> 00:28:23,278
Honestly, yes.

456
00:28:23,278 --> 00:28:25,927
I want to retire with the Dreams.

457
00:28:27,434 --> 00:28:31,779
This trade will happen.

458
00:28:32,563 --> 00:28:34,648
Definitely.

459
00:28:35,918 --> 00:28:37,584
Definitely.

460
00:28:52,533 --> 00:28:54,389
GM Ishikura.

461
00:29:00,295 --> 00:29:02,667
You're jumping the gun.

462
00:29:02,667 --> 00:29:06,680
I mean, talking about trades
before the Japan Series?

463
00:29:06,680 --> 00:29:09,617
The regular season has ended.

464
00:29:10,510 --> 00:29:11,995
Negotiations are fair game.

465
00:29:11,995 --> 00:29:14,043
Now hold on there.

466
00:29:14,043 --> 00:29:18,067
This season's last game just ended.

467
00:29:18,067 --> 00:29:20,936
Let us rest a little!

468
00:29:21,636 --> 00:29:23,948
Listen.

469
00:29:23,948 --> 00:29:25,643
We'll talk trades, later.

470
00:29:27,907 --> 00:29:30,128
Even if I were to trade...

471
00:29:31,203 --> 00:29:33,195
Kudo, our cleanup hitter?

472
00:29:37,799 --> 00:29:39,354
Kudo?

473
00:29:40,169 --> 00:29:43,594
Is that so?

474
00:29:43,594 --> 00:29:46,220
Does he really draw that much resentment?

475
00:29:46,220 --> 00:29:49,330
Yes, a maelstrom of resentment is raging.

476
00:29:49,330 --> 00:29:53,670
He's doing exactly as I expected.

477
00:30:04,426 --> 00:30:05,978
Hey!

478
00:30:12,370 --> 00:30:13,985
Kudo.

479
00:30:13,985 --> 00:30:16,098
Here.

480
00:30:16,098 --> 00:30:18,733
Catch it properly next time.

481
00:30:19,399 --> 00:30:20,858
Hey!

482
00:30:24,378 --> 00:30:28,208
The Dreams are my home.

483
00:30:29,447 --> 00:30:33,349
I've dedicated 11 years of my life
to this team.

484
00:30:33,349 --> 00:30:37,672
And now some baseball amateur
is trying to kick me out.

485
00:30:37,672 --> 00:30:39,467
Hey!

486
00:30:40,695 --> 00:30:42,661
See?

487
00:30:43,531 --> 00:30:46,046
You'd better catch it.

488
00:30:47,203 --> 00:30:48,849
Hey!

489
00:30:52,558 --> 00:30:55,831
Aw, man.

490
00:30:56,704 --> 00:30:59,608
Poor girl.

491
00:31:00,419 --> 00:31:01,630
Hey!

492
00:31:01,630 --> 00:31:03,297
Hey!

493
00:31:11,034 --> 00:31:12,495
Pick it up.

494
00:31:12,495 --> 00:31:14,324
It's for the repairs.

495
00:31:30,710 --> 00:31:32,731
Good work.

496
00:31:51,850 --> 00:31:53,626
What happened here?

497
00:31:53,626 --> 00:31:55,060
It was Kudo.

498
00:31:55,060 --> 00:31:56,424
Huh?

499
00:31:59,610 --> 00:32:01,564
Erm, the police...

500
00:32:01,564 --> 00:32:05,274
We can't turn over a player
who brings in money.

501
00:32:05,274 --> 00:32:06,235
But...

502
00:32:06,235 --> 00:32:07,911
For the sake of the team,

503
00:32:08,639 --> 00:32:10,605
I will sell him for a high price.

504
00:32:21,558 --> 00:32:25,271
But are you really trading Kudo?

505
00:32:25,271 --> 00:32:27,557
He's our star player.

506
00:32:27,557 --> 00:32:30,417
We don't need a rotten star.

507
00:32:32,318 --> 00:32:37,223
We've been together for so long.
I can't believe he's like that.

508
00:32:39,358 --> 00:32:42,385
Attachments and the likes
are unnecessary to win.

509
00:32:42,385 --> 00:32:45,143
Our staff are no exception to this rule.

510
00:32:45,143 --> 00:32:47,941
Huh? What do you mean?

511
00:32:47,941 --> 00:32:49,995
I mean nothing more than just that.

512
00:32:53,161 --> 00:32:55,750
This is pointless.

513
00:33:06,036 --> 00:33:08,725
Seems I'm being traded away.

514
00:33:08,725 --> 00:33:12,014
Huh? With who?

515
00:33:12,014 --> 00:33:14,110
A Vikings player.

516
00:33:14,110 --> 00:33:15,709
What?

517
00:33:16,849 --> 00:33:21,432
The new GM seems determined to get rid of me.

518
00:33:22,299 --> 00:33:25,330
What's he thinking?

519
00:33:32,629 --> 00:33:34,661
Here's your travel expense.

520
00:33:34,661 --> 00:33:36,447
No, it's fine.

521
00:33:36,447 --> 00:33:38,146
I insist.

522
00:33:39,126 --> 00:33:41,163
No, really.

523
00:33:42,840 --> 00:33:45,100
Please, it's on me.

524
00:34:00,072 --> 00:34:02,236
Look forward to the article.

525
00:34:02,236 --> 00:34:04,163
Thank you.

526
00:34:15,855 --> 00:34:17,690
Good morning.

527
00:34:18,527 --> 00:34:20,076
Prez.

528
00:34:21,328 --> 00:34:24,237
I need to talk to you.

529
00:34:24,237 --> 00:34:26,418
What? So formal.

530
00:34:26,418 --> 00:34:30,943
Are you and the GM close?

531
00:34:30,943 --> 00:34:32,063
What do you mean?

532
00:34:32,063 --> 00:34:34,198
Like, are you two an item?

533
00:34:35,186 --> 00:34:36,700
- Are you an idiot?
- Ow! It hurts!

534
00:34:36,700 --> 00:34:38,386
- Is that all you ever think about?
- Ow, ow...

535
00:34:38,386 --> 00:34:39,647
Ow! Please stop.

536
00:34:39,647 --> 00:34:40,877
Huh? What now?

537
00:34:40,877 --> 00:34:43,447
- I'll keep going until you get it.
- W-Wait, let me explain myself!

538
00:34:43,447 --> 00:34:45,726
Rumors say you two left the office together.

539
00:34:45,726 --> 00:34:47,373
- Says the gossip who spread them.
- Ouch!

540
00:34:47,373 --> 00:34:48,673
Ow! That actually hurts.

541
00:34:48,673 --> 00:34:49,883
- Are you sorry?
- Yes, ma'am.

542
00:34:49,883 --> 00:34:51,689
- Ow!
- You clearly aren't.

543
00:34:51,689 --> 00:34:52,829
Ow, that hurts!

544
00:34:52,829 --> 00:34:54,256
- Feel remorse!
- Yes, I understand.

545
00:34:54,256 --> 00:34:56,447
You're not even listening anymore.

546
00:34:56,447 --> 00:34:58,609
I'm just letting myself get hit!

547
00:34:58,609 --> 00:35:00,320
Pause, pause, pause.

548
00:35:00,320 --> 00:35:01,576
Huh?

549
00:35:05,394 --> 00:35:06,837
Huh?

550
00:35:07,797 --> 00:35:10,493
What's wrong?

551
00:35:10,493 --> 00:35:12,858
What? PC? A virus?

552
00:35:12,858 --> 00:35:15,365
A scoop! Look at the PC!

553
00:35:17,030 --> 00:35:21,400
[Batter K from Dreams]
[Traded for a Vikings benchwarmer]

554
00:35:22,676 --> 00:35:24,981
Huh? Seriously?

555
00:35:24,981 --> 00:35:26,578
Yes, I'm sorry.

556
00:35:26,578 --> 00:35:27,895
Yes, this is Miyahara.

557
00:35:27,895 --> 00:35:28,745
[They're definitely talking about Kudo]
[Is the GM an amateur?]

558
00:35:29,596 --> 00:35:30,460
Thank you for your cooperation.

559
00:35:30,460 --> 00:35:31,864
- Dreams management, speaking.
- Thank you.

560
00:35:31,864 --> 00:35:33,415
[Under that amateur Sakurazaki,
it's really the end for Dreams]

561
00:35:33,415 --> 00:35:34,775
[Dreams isn't Dreams without Kudo!]
[This Sakurazaki should just quit]

562
00:35:40,540 --> 00:35:42,460
[Critics say "The new GM ought to quit"]

563
00:35:44,515 --> 00:35:46,370
[Voices of betrayal over Dreams trade]

564
00:35:46,370 --> 00:35:47,570
[President of Baseball Operations]

565
00:35:52,040 --> 00:35:54,998
No, there's no such trade discussion.

566
00:35:54,998 --> 00:35:56,537
The article is a hoax.

567
00:35:56,537 --> 00:35:58,731
You're persistent!

568
00:35:58,731 --> 00:36:00,365
Why don't they believe us?

569
00:36:00,365 --> 00:36:02,663
I've had it.

570
00:36:02,663 --> 00:36:04,064
I'm going.

571
00:36:04,064 --> 00:36:04,997
Where to?

572
00:36:04,997 --> 00:36:06,445
To the GM.

573
00:36:06,445 --> 00:36:07,690
Then I'm coming too.

574
00:36:07,690 --> 00:36:10,442
I have a thing or two I want to say myself.

575
00:36:10,442 --> 00:36:12,724
- Then let's all go!
- Yeah, let's go!

576
00:36:12,724 --> 00:36:13,931
Huh? Wait a minute, please.

577
00:36:13,931 --> 00:36:15,914
Well, maybe I'll go too.

578
00:36:15,914 --> 00:36:17,444
Huh? Where's everyone going?

579
00:36:17,444 --> 00:36:20,320
To the GM. We're going to tell him
we're against the trade.

580
00:36:20,320 --> 00:36:21,346
Without me?

581
00:36:21,346 --> 00:36:24,223
Yes. Because you two are, you know...

582
00:36:25,908 --> 00:36:29,456
I stood up to him. Did you forget?

583
00:36:29,456 --> 00:36:30,884
No, ma'am.

584
00:36:30,884 --> 00:36:33,448
I remember your knuckle sandwich
clear as day.

585
00:36:33,448 --> 00:36:35,920
Ow! My eyeball!

586
00:36:35,920 --> 00:36:38,035
We have something to discuss.

587
00:36:39,026 --> 00:36:40,609
Ah, GM.

588
00:36:41,690 --> 00:36:43,715
What is it?

589
00:36:43,715 --> 00:36:47,099
Why are you letting Kudo go?

590
00:36:47,099 --> 00:36:48,510
Are you rallying on his orders?

591
00:36:48,510 --> 00:36:50,167
No.

592
00:36:50,167 --> 00:36:54,059
Then meet me in the meeting space in an hour.

593
00:36:55,487 --> 00:36:56,993
Excuse me.

594
00:37:01,862 --> 00:37:05,803
Yikes. I can practically
taste the bloodlust in here.

595
00:37:05,803 --> 00:37:07,192
Can you blame us?

596
00:37:07,192 --> 00:37:09,286
He's trading our star player for a nobody.

597
00:37:09,286 --> 00:37:10,719
Let's calm down.

598
00:37:10,719 --> 00:37:13,707
It's like you're itching for a throw down.

599
00:37:13,707 --> 00:37:14,572
How so?

600
00:37:14,572 --> 00:37:16,084
There! That knuckle!

601
00:37:17,348 --> 00:37:20,173
Alright then, let's begin.

602
00:37:21,620 --> 00:37:23,840
[Reasons for Letting Kudo Go]

603
00:37:26,560 --> 00:37:31,170
[Reasons for Letting Kudo Go]

604
00:37:31,909 --> 00:37:35,016
First, he's weak in clutch situations.

605
00:37:35,776 --> 00:37:39,124
Kudo can't hit in clutch situations.

606
00:37:39,124 --> 00:37:44,118
What? No, no, no.

607
00:37:44,886 --> 00:37:47,000
Whose Kudo are you talking about?

608
00:37:47,000 --> 00:37:49,661
What do you know about our Kudo?

609
00:37:49,661 --> 00:37:51,226
Right?

610
00:37:51,226 --> 00:37:53,965
I could laugh at how absurd that sounds.

611
00:38:00,576 --> 00:38:03,078
Looking at his batting average
and home runs,

612
00:38:03,078 --> 00:38:05,185
he seems like a valuable player.

613
00:38:05,185 --> 00:38:08,471
His batting average with runners
in scoring position is a .307.

614
00:38:08,471 --> 00:38:10,428
I don't think he's weak
in clutch situations.

615
00:38:10,428 --> 00:38:11,965
Exactly.

616
00:38:11,965 --> 00:38:13,908
- Don't just sit there.
- Ow!

617
00:38:13,908 --> 00:38:16,901
That's right! What they said!

618
00:38:16,901 --> 00:38:20,374
Kudo has made five game-winning hits.

619
00:38:21,643 --> 00:38:23,494
He's only third on the team.

620
00:38:25,028 --> 00:38:28,744
Despite a .330 batting average,
he has too few game-winning hits.

621
00:38:28,744 --> 00:38:32,317
He can't deliver results in crucial moments.

622
00:38:32,317 --> 00:38:34,797
He's a weak hitter in clutch situations.

623
00:38:35,486 --> 00:38:36,583
Talk back to him!

624
00:38:36,583 --> 00:38:38,926
Huh? Me?

625
00:38:38,926 --> 00:38:40,942
He's not weak in clutch situations!

626
00:38:40,942 --> 00:38:44,362
You see... I'm Kudo's...

627
00:38:44,362 --> 00:38:45,509
Cheerleader!

628
00:38:45,509 --> 00:38:48,202
Oh, God, Buddha, Kudo!

629
00:38:48,202 --> 00:38:49,505
Hit it out of the park!

630
00:38:49,505 --> 00:38:51,537
We don't need reassurance from a cheerleader.

631
00:38:51,537 --> 00:38:52,980
Say something sensible.

632
00:38:52,980 --> 00:38:53,880
Right?

633
00:38:53,880 --> 00:38:54,814
R-Right.

634
00:38:54,814 --> 00:38:56,873
Just calm down for a moment.

635
00:38:56,873 --> 00:38:59,393
- He has his good points...
- Let's hear him out first.

636
00:38:59,393 --> 00:39:02,425
- Sit down, sit down.
- Yes, sir.

637
00:39:04,735 --> 00:39:08,820
Second, his big plays
are relatively low-impact.

638
00:39:08,820 --> 00:39:10,950
Kudo is weak in the heat.

639
00:39:12,633 --> 00:39:16,872
He performs poorly in the summer,
especially at outdoor stadiums.

640
00:39:16,872 --> 00:39:20,855
Summer is a crucial period
for determining standings.

641
00:39:20,855 --> 00:39:23,907
Yet he can't produce results
during these crucial times.

642
00:39:27,603 --> 00:39:30,178
What's the point in hitting home runs

643
00:39:30,178 --> 00:39:32,179
after last place has been determined?

644
00:39:34,767 --> 00:39:36,977
He's really studied baseball.

645
00:39:36,977 --> 00:39:40,252
Yes. And quite thoroughly too...

646
00:39:40,252 --> 00:39:43,692
Prez, say something back!

647
00:39:43,692 --> 00:39:45,470
Where's all that momentum you had?

648
00:39:45,470 --> 00:39:47,149
Just be quiet.

649
00:39:47,149 --> 00:39:48,365
Yes, ma'am.

650
00:39:49,089 --> 00:39:51,617
Third, the new standard for baseballs.

651
00:39:51,617 --> 00:39:54,620
As you all know, starting next season,

652
00:39:54,620 --> 00:39:57,388
we'll be using a rebound foam ball
that doesn't fly as far.

653
00:39:57,388 --> 00:40:01,075
The flight distance is said to drop
by 5 to 10 meters.

654
00:40:02,244 --> 00:40:06,254
If that happens, Kudo's home runs...

655
00:40:07,220 --> 00:40:09,217
will decrease by 16.

656
00:40:10,995 --> 00:40:14,070
He would no longer be a long-ball hitter,

657
00:40:14,070 --> 00:40:16,174
but a mid-range hitter.

658
00:40:17,309 --> 00:40:18,810
In other words,

659
00:40:19,454 --> 00:40:21,621
if the ball doesn't fly as far,

660
00:40:23,815 --> 00:40:26,584
his utility becomes ambiguous.

661
00:40:31,983 --> 00:40:35,063
Fourth, a generational change.

662
00:40:35,710 --> 00:40:38,038
Kudo's career will be short.

663
00:40:38,038 --> 00:40:39,815
But fortunately,

664
00:40:39,815 --> 00:40:42,850
we have many promising players
who can replace him.

665
00:40:43,917 --> 00:40:46,030
[#59 Kotaro Sakakibara]
[Batting average: 0.327 - Home runs: 9]

666
00:40:46,030 --> 00:40:47,340
[#70 Koji Miyamoto]
[Batting average: 0.314 - Home runs: 16]

667
00:40:47,340 --> 00:40:48,725
[#72 Kaito Tokoro]
[Batting average: 0.301 - Home runs: 8]

668
00:40:48,725 --> 00:40:50,405
[#59 Junji Honda]
[Batting average 0.269 - Home runs: 8]

669
00:40:53,686 --> 00:40:55,305
What do you all think?

670
00:41:02,266 --> 00:41:04,189
And fifth.

671
00:41:07,083 --> 00:41:09,235
This is the biggest reason.

672
00:41:10,005 --> 00:41:12,864
[Reason 5: Throws the team in disarray]

673
00:41:12,864 --> 00:41:17,437
Kudo is eroding the team.

674
00:41:21,593 --> 00:41:23,410
Pitchers, gather 'round!

675
00:41:23,410 --> 00:41:25,669
Yes, sir.

676
00:41:25,669 --> 00:41:27,377
- Hurry up!
- Yes, sir.

677
00:41:27,377 --> 00:41:30,693
What are you guys doing, huh?

678
00:41:30,693 --> 00:41:33,385
You good-for-nothings!

679
00:41:33,385 --> 00:41:36,847
Hey! Why'd you let them make a comeback?

680
00:41:36,847 --> 00:41:38,749
Are you underestimating pros?

681
00:41:38,749 --> 00:41:40,727
- Hey!
- Hey, Kudo!

682
00:41:41,372 --> 00:41:42,570
Huh?

683
00:41:42,570 --> 00:41:44,770
Baseball is a team sport!

684
00:41:44,770 --> 00:41:47,058
Pitchers cover for batters
when they can't hit.

685
00:41:47,058 --> 00:41:49,409
We each cover the other. That's how it works.

686
00:41:51,712 --> 00:41:55,072
Keep it to yourself, you bastard!

687
00:41:58,787 --> 00:42:00,973
Sawada pitched for Dreams
until two years ago.

688
00:42:00,973 --> 00:42:03,539
Despite securing 15 wins for the team,

689
00:42:03,539 --> 00:42:07,978
he had to leave the Dreams to protect Kudo.

690
00:42:09,690 --> 00:42:13,400
Sawada didn't say a word
in his own defense, did he?

691
00:42:24,782 --> 00:42:30,107
The reason Kudo clings to the Dreams
is not love.

692
00:42:31,362 --> 00:42:34,461
It's because it's a team he can control.

693
00:42:36,251 --> 00:42:39,076
Kudo is the star of the Dreams.

694
00:42:39,076 --> 00:42:41,537
If the player with the most fans leaves,

695
00:42:41,537 --> 00:42:43,623
tickets and merchandise won't sell.

696
00:42:43,623 --> 00:42:45,056
That's absolutely right!

697
00:42:45,056 --> 00:42:46,434
Go, Hiromi!

698
00:42:46,434 --> 00:42:48,155
- Give it to him!
- Quiet!

699
00:42:48,155 --> 00:42:51,384
Indeed, the presence of a star player
is important.

700
00:42:51,384 --> 00:42:56,231
That is why I'll bring in a player
to replace him.

701
00:42:56,231 --> 00:43:00,128
Huh? There's no one who can replace Kudo!

702
00:43:00,128 --> 00:43:01,457
But there is.

703
00:43:01,457 --> 00:43:03,556
And I believe you all know him well.

704
00:43:07,164 --> 00:43:09,405
This infamous star player...

705
00:43:10,313 --> 00:43:14,210
was forced off the team because of Kudo.

706
00:43:15,736 --> 00:43:17,338
No way...

707
00:43:18,031 --> 00:43:21,314
President Makita,
please have Sawada's uniform ready.

708
00:43:22,052 --> 00:43:23,463
He's coming back?

709
00:43:23,463 --> 00:43:25,417
To the Dreams?

710
00:43:25,417 --> 00:43:27,550
The trade has already been finalized.

711
00:43:28,225 --> 00:43:30,350
Wow! Seriously?

712
00:43:30,350 --> 00:43:32,603
Sawada will be returning to the Dreams.

713
00:43:37,908 --> 00:43:40,381
You know about WAR, yes?
[T/N: "Wins Above Replacement"]

714
00:43:40,381 --> 00:43:44,583
Sawada is top of the league, at a 7.5.

715
00:43:44,583 --> 00:43:48,295
Did the Vikings really let Sawada go?

716
00:43:49,234 --> 00:43:50,605
Yes.

717
00:43:52,082 --> 00:43:54,927
You're offering up Kudo?

718
00:43:54,927 --> 00:43:58,233
But Sawada is a pitcher who represents Japan.

719
00:43:58,987 --> 00:44:03,200
Sawada has a losing record
against the top-ranking Pelicans.

720
00:44:03,200 --> 00:44:06,965
And Kudo's useless in the summer.
He only hits well in autumn.

721
00:44:07,681 --> 00:44:10,057
Isn't a player who hits in autumn

722
00:44:10,057 --> 00:44:12,553
necessary for a team who's always in second?

723
00:44:12,553 --> 00:44:16,863
No, we need a player
who hits well on average.

724
00:44:18,329 --> 00:44:20,107
His batting average
against the Pelicans is...

725
00:44:20,107 --> 00:44:21,992
I know.

726
00:44:21,992 --> 00:44:23,913
A .420 batting average.

727
00:44:25,523 --> 00:44:27,140
As expected.

728
00:44:27,140 --> 00:44:32,965
Moreover, he has great chemistry
with the Pelicans' home stadium.

729
00:44:32,965 --> 00:44:34,486
No, that's...

730
00:44:41,848 --> 00:44:45,376
Anyone against the trade?

731
00:44:54,726 --> 00:44:56,585
Anyone?

732
00:45:00,213 --> 00:45:03,802
Then I'm done here.

733
00:45:10,750 --> 00:45:14,200
Sawada is coming back, huh?

734
00:45:14,200 --> 00:45:16,481
This is going to be busy.

735
00:45:16,481 --> 00:45:19,194
A miracle is happening.

736
00:45:19,194 --> 00:45:21,754
Ow, ow, ow! Hey, that hurts!

737
00:45:21,754 --> 00:45:23,406
Wait, don't tell me.

738
00:45:23,406 --> 00:45:25,555
I get hit even when things are going well?

739
00:45:25,555 --> 00:45:28,309
Why can't it be one or the other?

740
00:45:28,309 --> 00:45:29,829
Why?

741
00:45:45,610 --> 00:45:47,842
Please clear out your locker.

742
00:45:55,561 --> 00:45:57,264
Right now.

743
00:46:06,436 --> 00:46:09,035
I paid for the repairs myself.

744
00:46:12,487 --> 00:46:14,840
Don't get carried away.

745
00:46:15,771 --> 00:46:20,772
It ought to go without saying,
but be polite over there.

746
00:46:23,448 --> 00:46:28,304
I'm a homegrown star,
a candidate for a retired number.

747
00:46:29,079 --> 00:46:31,140
You'll turn the fans against you.

748
00:46:32,348 --> 00:46:37,203
Sawada is returning to pitch for the Dreams.

749
00:46:37,203 --> 00:46:39,508
- Sawada?
- Yes.

750
00:46:41,067 --> 00:46:45,252
He is more deserving of a retired number.

751
00:46:46,173 --> 00:46:50,458
He has real accomplishments,
and is admired by everyone.

752
00:46:50,458 --> 00:46:52,945
He's even a future manager candidate.

753
00:46:53,951 --> 00:46:55,573
You.

754
00:46:55,573 --> 00:46:58,958
Who do you think I am? Huh?

755
00:46:58,958 --> 00:47:01,695
I can crush you anytime!

756
00:47:01,695 --> 00:47:04,271
Next time, it won't just be your car!

757
00:47:05,357 --> 00:47:06,876
Kudo...

758
00:47:42,724 --> 00:47:45,161
Welcome back! We've been waiting!

759
00:47:51,507 --> 00:47:52,888
Thank you!

760
00:47:53,932 --> 00:47:56,647
Sawada is back with the Dreams!

761
00:47:57,369 --> 00:47:59,627
Sawada, who has returned to the Dreams,

762
00:47:59,627 --> 00:48:01,737
is welcomed with glee by the fans.

763
00:48:01,737 --> 00:48:05,089
Great things are expected of him next season.

764
00:48:05,089 --> 00:48:06,732
<i>In 2024, Sawada was traded away...</i>

765
00:48:06,732 --> 00:48:08,937
- Yay!
- What now?

766
00:48:08,937 --> 00:48:10,817
- Alright, alright!
- Huh? What?

767
00:48:10,817 --> 00:48:11,825
Too close.

768
00:48:11,825 --> 00:48:13,829
- Hey, Miyu.
- What, what, what?

769
00:48:13,829 --> 00:48:18,387
Maybe if things go well,

770
00:48:18,387 --> 00:48:21,574
the Dreams might not be last next year!

771
00:48:21,574 --> 00:48:22,725
- Yay!
- I see.

772
00:48:22,725 --> 00:48:25,505
Nothing's started yet, though.

773
00:48:25,505 --> 00:48:27,034
I don't care. Praise me.

774
00:48:27,034 --> 00:48:29,634
What brought on this strange attitude?

775
00:48:29,634 --> 00:48:31,216
Huh? Did you work hard?

776
00:48:31,216 --> 00:48:34,530
Yes, you're great, you're great! Amazing!

777
00:48:43,116 --> 00:48:44,976
I'm home.

778
00:48:59,214 --> 00:49:00,992
What are you doing?

779
00:49:00,992 --> 00:49:02,552
Jun.

780
00:49:06,271 --> 00:49:09,662
If there are any technical terms
you don't understand, just ask.

781
00:49:11,051 --> 00:49:13,158
Don't look through my files
without permission.

782
00:49:14,932 --> 00:49:16,325
Sorry.

783
00:49:34,470 --> 00:49:41,040
[Rookies from 2020~2026]

784
00:50:18,683 --> 00:50:21,250
Well, regarding this trade...

785
00:50:21,250 --> 00:50:26,662
As a comrade, I couldn't help
but support your work.

786
00:50:28,710 --> 00:50:34,170
The Dreams recorded 56 wins this year.

787
00:50:34,170 --> 00:50:38,595
Before that, it was 59 wins.

788
00:50:38,595 --> 00:50:42,674
Don't you think that's too many victories?

789
00:50:51,574 --> 00:50:56,730
Why do you think I hired you?

790
00:51:05,001 --> 00:51:09,368
Because you have a unique resume.

791
00:51:10,943 --> 00:51:14,132
Win, disband.

792
00:51:14,132 --> 00:51:16,889
Win, disband.

793
00:51:16,889 --> 00:51:21,288
Win, then disband.

794
00:51:28,753 --> 00:51:33,037
Please follow your resume.

795
00:51:33,037 --> 00:51:34,527
Alright?

796
00:51:38,212 --> 00:51:40,049
Understood.

797
00:52:10,189 --> 00:52:11,534
Good morning.

798
00:52:11,534 --> 00:52:13,148
Good morning.

799
00:52:13,148 --> 00:52:16,919
Everyone from the scouting department,
to my office in 5 minutes.

800
00:52:18,331 --> 00:52:19,697
Yes, sir.

801
00:52:21,805 --> 00:52:22,948
For the past few years,

802
00:52:22,948 --> 00:52:26,195
the performance of our top draft picks
has been disappointing.

803
00:52:27,162 --> 00:52:30,957
It's reasonable to assume
there are some questionable picks.

804
00:52:30,957 --> 00:52:34,929
But many players don't succeed
even among first-round picks.

805
00:52:34,929 --> 00:52:37,789
President Makita is right, you know.

806
00:52:39,039 --> 00:52:41,528
There might be a scout committing fraud.

807
00:52:41,528 --> 00:52:42,333
What?

808
00:52:42,333 --> 00:52:45,649
Now wait a second.
Where's the evidence?

809
00:52:46,337 --> 00:52:50,669
In one hour,
we'll have a meeting for the draft.

